%N A122952 Decimal expansion of 3*Pi.
%C A122952 Area of the unit cycloid with cusp at the origin, whose parametric formula is x = t - sin(t) and y = 1 - cos(t).
%C A122952 The arc length Integral_{theta=0..2*Pi} sqrt(2(1-cos(theta))) (d theta) = 8.
%C A122952 3*Pi is also the surface area of a sphere whose diameter equals the square root of 3. More generally x*Pi is also the surface area of a sphere whose diameter equals the square root of x. - _Omar E. Pol_, Dec 18 2013
%C A122952 3*Pi is also the area of the nephroid (an epicycloid with two cusps) whose Cartesian parametrization is: x = (1/2) * (3*cos(t) - cos(3t)) and y = (1/2) * (3*sin(t) - sin(3t)). The length of this nephroid is 12. See the curve at the Mathcurve link. - _Bernard Schott_, Feb 01 2020
